title: KMC King of the Mountain Challenge - CamRock
description: The KMC King of the Mountain Challenge is a unique mountain bike hill climb/time trial event with riders racing in waves of 10-15 against each other and the clock.
course:
-  Off-road double and single track, 70-85% uphill, approximately 4-5 minutes in duration
-
registration: Register online at https://www.swiftentry.com/ before midnight May 25 or onsite day-of.
notes: KMC podium-payback - Award winners who competed with a KMC Chain on their bike will receive an entry fee reimbursement.
directions: From East (Milwaukee I94): Take Exit 267 @ Johnson Creek,  Go South on Hwy. 26, Turn Right onto Hwy. 18, Turn Left onto N Main St in Cambridge, Turn Right at Spring St/Cty Rd B/Water St.  From North/West (Interstate 90): Take US-12E/UW-18 E, Turn on to Spring Street in Cambridge, Continue onto Cty Rd B/Water St.  From South (Illinois): Take Exit 160 onto WI-73, Head North then Turn Right onto Cty Rd B/Water St. GPS Address: 2334 Highland Drive, Cambridge, WI  53523

title: Polish Moon Ride
description: A family-friendly, police-led fun ride on urban streets.

title: JDRF Ride to Cure - La Crosse
John Hatherly Mid Century Ride - Waupaca
description: Non competitive ride has been going for 5 years.  Multiple distances open to all ages.  Two well stocked rest stops centrally located on flower pedal design course.
course: Flower pedal course allows you build your own distances including 12, 20, 30, 50, 62, 70 and 100 miles.
registration: Go to www.321goevents.com or www.active.com to register.
notes: This race has donated over $175,000 in 5 years to Waupaca High School in the form of scholarships to graduating seniors.
